question: 三つ編み
sourceMnemonic: <ja>編む</ja> is "to knit." When you knit in <kanji>three</kanji>s, you are knitting in a braid style. What do you braid? Hair. That makes this <vocabulary>braided hair</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: The reading is the <ja>み</ja> from <ja>三つ</ja> and <ja>つ</ja> and <ja>編む</ja> combined into one (or should I say three?) braids. Just watch out because this isn't <ja>みっつあみ</ja>, it's just <ja>みつあみ</ja>. Listen to the audio a few times to make sure you remember how it's spelled and pronounced!
